            <h2>Light Box</h2>

            <p class="lead">Poet Robert Crawford and photographer Norman McBeath partner to celebrate the 2015 UNESCO International Year of Light.</p>

            <p>When 2015 was announced as the UNESCO International Year of Light, the news stoked a spark in the brain of academic and poet Robert Crawford. Having long been inspired by light and science — his 1990 poetry debut, <em><a href="">A Scottish Assembly</a></em> weaves together lines on light and love and incorporates tongue-twisting scientific references — the spark was fanned into an idea of an artistic collaboration of poet, photographer and physicist.</p>

